My friend introduced me to mun patio and I am just obsessed! From their service to their food, I'm going to have to give them five stars! They are banchan is super fresh and pairs well with everything that is so served on the menu.The service here are so sweet and attentive! As a Southern girl, hospitality is a major component in rating a restaurant and mun patio exceeded my expectations! Shout out to Esther and the servers for making my experience at mun well worth the drive from the west side!!The space is out in the courtyard with a bunch of tables, portable grills and in the corner they have a self service room and bar, which is complementary for guest who eat at the patio.I wasn't able to grab a picture, but at the end they make you the famous Korean fried rice with the meat, and a bunch of cheese!This is a great place to have get together's with your friends or go on a date. Also, I forgot to mention their drinks are phenomenal!Just a little tip on the weekends they don't take reservations so I'll try to come for an early dinner so you don't have to wait ! Cheers!
